Description:

This plugin exposes vdr status information via a websocket connection.

Required packages:
Arch Linux:    nlohmann-json
Debian/Ubuntu: nlohmann-json3-dev
SuSE:          nlohmann_json-devel


Configuration:

  -p PORT,  --port=PORT     port for the websocket server (default: 6742)
  -l DIR,   --logodir=DIR   path for channel logos folder (default: /var/lib/vdr/channellogos/)
  -w WEBDIR --webdir=WEBDIR path for the webfrontend that should be served by the plugin's webserver

Copy the config/allowed_hosts.conf file to the plugin's configdir, e.g. /var/lib/vdr/plugins/websocket/allowed_hosts.conf and adapt it to your needs.

Frontends:

https://github.com/seahawk1986/vdr-websocket-status is an example Client for vdr-plugin-websocket
